<COREF ID="14" TYPE="IDENT">The report</COREF> observed that if economic and banking policies are effective , <COREF ID="11" TYPE="IDENT">the economies of <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">the Asian region</COREF></COREF> hopefully would start rising again in 1999 , but <COREF ID="11" TYPE="IDENT">they</COREF> would not be likely to exhibit a large , high - speed , V - shaped rise like that of Mexico and Argentina following the fiscal crisis of 1994 - 1995 .
